# Local development needs NO env vars — the app runs an embedded Postgres
# (PGlite) with data stored in ./.local-pg, and applies the schema automatically.
#
# For production (Vercel), use Neon Postgres:
#   Easiest: in your Vercel project, Storage tab → add Neon. Vercel sets the
#   connection string for you (as DATABASE_URL / POSTGRES_URL) — nothing to paste.
#   Or create one at https://neon.tech and copy its connection string here.
#
# Create the tables once against that database:
#   DATABASE_URL="postgres://…" pnpm db:push

DATABASE_URL=
